  "name": "Acandia Hotel",
  "description": "Hotel Acandia is an excellent choice for travelers visiting Rhodes Town, offering a romantic environment alongside many helpful amenities designed to enhance your stay. Hotel Acandia is a romantic hotel offering a refrigerator and air conditioning in the rooms. Plus, guests can enjoy an on-site restaurant, which has made this a popular choice among travelers visiting Rhodes Town. Nearby landmarks such as Mandraki Harbour (0.2 mi) and Deer Statues (0.2 mi) make Hotel Acandia a great place to stay when visiting Rhodes Town. When you’re feeling hungry, be sure to check out Wonder, My Thai, and Louis, which are some restaurants that are popular with locals and out-of-towners alike. If you’re looking for something to do, Palace of the Grand Master of the Knights of Rhodes (0.5 mi), Archaeological Museum of Rhodes (Hospital of the Knights) (0.6 mi), and The Acropolis of Rhodes (1.0 mi) are a nice way to spend some time, and they are all within walking distance of Hotel Acandia. Enjoy your stay in Rhodes Town!",
